P_A(B)
B
A
P(B|A)
U
V
P(U\cap V)=P(U)P(V)
P(U|V)=P(U)
P(V)>0
P(A|B)P(B)=P(A\cap B)
A=\left\{ \left(r,b\right)\in S\mid r\text{ odd}\right\} 
B=\left\{ \left(r,b\right)\in S\mid b\text{ even}\right\} 
S=\left\{ \left(r,b\right)\mid r,b\in\left\{ 1,2,3,4,5,6\right\} \right\} 
\left(r,b\right)\in S
P\left(A\right)=\frac{\left|A\right|}{\left|S\right|}=\frac{18}{36}=\frac{1}{2}
P\left(B\right)=\frac{\left|B\right|}{\left|S\right|}=\frac{18}{36}=\frac{1}{2}
A\cap B=\left\{ \left(r,b\right)\in S\mid r\text{ odd}\wedge b\text{ even}\right\} 
P\left(A\cap B\right)=\frac{\left|A\cap B\right|}{\left|S\right|}=\frac{9}{36}=\frac{1}{4}
P_{A}\left(B\right)=\frac{P\left(A\cap B\right)}{P\left(B\right)}=\frac{\frac{1}{4}}{\frac{1}{2}}=\frac{1}{2}
P_{A}\left(B\right)=P\left(B\right)
A
B
